{"schema_version":"1.7.3","id":"OESA-2023-1866","published":"2023-12-01T11:06:22Z","modified":"2025-09-03T06:19:31.028772Z","upstream":["CVE-2023-45661","CVE-2023-45664"],"summary":"stb security update","details":"Single-file public domain libraries for C/C++.\r\n\r\nSecurity Fix(es):\r\n\r\nstb_image is a single file MIT licensed library for processing images. A crafted image file may trigger out of bounds memcpy read in `stbi__gif_load_next`. This happens because two_back points to a memory address lower than the start of the buffer out. This issue may be used to leak internal memory allocation information.(CVE-2023-45661)\r\n\r\nstb_image is a single file MIT licensed library for processing images. A crafted image file can trigger `stbi__load_gif_main_outofmem` attempt to double-free the out variable. This happens in `stbi__load_gif_main` because when the `layers * stride` value is zero the behavior is implementation defined, but common that realloc frees the old memory and returns null pointer. Since it attempts to double-free the memory a few lines below the first “free”, the issue can be potentially exploited only in a multi-threaded environment. In the worst case this may lead to code execution.(CVE-2023-45664)","affected":[{"package":{"name":"stb","ecosystem":"openEuler:22.03-LTS-SP2","purl":"pkg:rpm/openEuler/stb&distro=openEuler-22.03-LTS-SP2"},"ranges":[{"type":"ECOSYSTEM","events":[{"introduced":"0"},{"fixed":"0.20220908git8b5f1f3-0.8.oe2203sp2"}]}],"ecosystem_specific":{"aarch64":["stb_ds-devel-0.67.20220908git8b5f1f3-0.8.oe2203sp2.aarch64.rpm","stb_voxel_render-devel-0.89.20220908git8b5f1f3-0.8.oe2203sp2.aarch64.rpm","stb_image_write-devel-1.16.20220908git8b5f1f3-0.8.oe2203sp2.aarch64.rpm","stb_dxt-devel-1.12.20220908git8b5f1f3-0.8.oe2203sp2.aarch64.rpm","stb_herringbone_wang_tile-devel-0.7.20220908git8b5f1f3-0.8.oe2203sp2.aarch64.rpm","stb_divide-devel-0.94.20220908git8b5f1f3-0.8.oe2203sp2.aarch64.rpm","stb_connected_components-devel-0.96.20220908git8